---
import { Image } from '@astrojs/image/components';
import Aws from '../components/icons/aws.astro';
import Electron from '../components/icons/electron.astro';
import Github from '../components/icons/github.astro';
import Laravel from '../components/icons/laravel.astro';
import Pulumi from '../components/icons/pulumi.astro';
import React from '../components/icons/react.astro';
import Typescript from '../components/icons/typescript.astro';

import BaseLayout from '../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout>
	<main class="px-6 md:px-0 max-w-xl m-auto">
        <h1 class="text-5xl mb-4">Projects</h1>
        
        <hr class="mb-10" />
        
        <article class="mb-20">
            <Image src="/img/saturn-time-tracking.png" alt="Get Saturn Time Tracking App" width={575} height={250} class="rounded-lg mb-6" />
			<h2 class="text-4xl mb-3">
                <a href="https://getsaturnapp.com" target="_blank">Saturn Time Tracker App</a>
            </h2>
			<p>A simple yet effective React App for tracking time across multiple projects. Saturn includes an API for syncing time entries across platforms as well as integrations like JIRA Server. This was born as an upgrade from my previous Project Timer time tracking app</p>

            <h4 class="text-xl mt-5 mb-2">Tech Stack</h4>
            <ul class="flex space-x-3 items-center">
                <li><a  target="_blank" href="http://www.typescriptlang.org/" title="TypeScript"><Typescript class="h-5" /><span class="sr-only">TypeScript</span></a></li>
                <li><a  target="_blank" href="https://reactjs.org/" title="React"><React class="h-5" /><span class="sr-only">React</span></a></li>
                <li><a  target="_blank" href="http://laravel.com/" title="Laravel"><Laravel class="h-5" /><span class="sr-only">Laravel</span></a></li>
                <li><a  target="_blank" href="https://www.pulumi.com/" title="Pulumi"><Pulumi class="h-5" /><span class="sr-only">Pulumi</span></a></li>
                <li><a  target="_blank" href="https://aws.amazon.com/" title="AWS"><Aws class="w-7" /><span class="sr-only">AWS</span></a></li>
            </ul>
		</article>

        <article class="mb-20">
            <Image src="/img/project-timer.png" alt="Project Timer" width={575} height={250} class="rounded-lg mb-6" />
			<h2 class="text-4xl mb-3">
                <a href="https://alxmerino.github.io/Project-Timer" target="_blank">Project Timer</a>
            </h2>

			<p>When I first started tracking time for my projects I was overwhelme by the existing time tracking apps. Some were overly complicated others just weren't enought. I created Project Timer to have a simple to use time tracking tool with features exactly as I needed them.</p>

            <h4 class="text-xl mt-5 mb-2">Tech Stack</h4>
            <ul class="flex space-x-3 items-center">
                <li><a  target="_blank" href="https://github.com/Alxmerino/Project-Timer" title="See Project Code"><Github class="h-5" /><span class="sr-only">See Project Code</span></a></li>
                <li><a  target="_blank" href="https://reactjs.org/" class="React"><React class="h-5" /><span class="sr-only">React</span></a></li>
                <li><a  target="_blank" href="https://www.electronjs.org/" class="Electron"><Electron class="h-5" /><span class="sr-only">Electron</span></a></li>
            </ul>
		</article>
		
	</main>
</BaseLayout>